subSubSection.paragraph:
Sigmas II (
Fig. 118g
), thin, often more or less symmetrical, variable in size, 14– 22.1 – 32 µm .

One record from India (
Lakwal et al. 2018
) is a blackish mass of lobed tubes, which is definitely not the present species. Lacking a description this specimen from the Ratnagiri coast of Northwest India remains unidentified.

We compared spicule sizes of West Pacific and Indian Ocean specimens (cf. 
Table 8
) and concluded that there is hardly any regional difference; perhaps the length range of the toxas in West Pacific specimens (
18–111 µm
) exceeds that of the Indian Ocean specimens.
